# Python Standards

## Project Structure
- Tests in `tests/` directory
- Detect dependency tooling from repo files (`pyproject.toml`, `requirements.txt`, `uv.lock`, etc.) — never assume pip, uv, poetry, or any specific tool

## Code Style
- Black formatting (88 char line length)
- PEP 8 naming: `snake_case` functions/variables, `PascalCase` classes, `UPPER_CASE` constants
- Absolute imports over relative

## Type Hints
- Type all function parameters and return values

## Documentation
- Google-style docstrings for public APIs

## Logging & Errors
- Prefer stdlib `logging` over `print()` for application output — adopt the project's existing logger when one is present
- Specific try-except blocks (no bare except)
- Clear, actionable error messages
